<item>
            <title>[LU-5817] cl_put_grouplock()) ASSERTION( cg-&gt;cg_gid ) failed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5817</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a group lock with GID=0 is released (put_grouplock is called), an assertion in cl_put_grouplock is hit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are two assertions at the start of cl_put_grouplock:&lt;br/&gt;
        LASSERT(cg-&amp;gt;cg_env);&lt;br/&gt;
        LASSERT(cg-&amp;gt;cg_gid);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cg_env is a pointer, so this assertion is valid, but cg_gid is just an integer so this is not a valid assertion.  There are no other checks to make sure the GID is not zero, so a zero a GID is otherwise valid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since there doesn&apos;t appear to be any reason a &apos;0&apos; GID shouldn&apos;t be allowed, the solution is to remove this assertion.  I&apos;ll make a patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any 2.x version of Lustre.  Client crash.</environment>
